WEBVTT

00:04.963 --> 00:07.549
(gentle music)

00:31.573 --> 00:33.450
- [Mr. Black] Come on, Sam.

00:33.450 --> 00:35.285
Wake up, little boy.

00:35.285 --> 00:37.495
Sleepy time's over.

00:37.495 --> 00:38.913
Yo, Mr. Paxton.

00:39.831 --> 00:40.915
Come on Sam,

00:40.915 --> 00:43.001
don't make me have to
start chopping limbs here.

00:44.711 --> 00:45.545
Come on.

00:45.545 --> 00:47.505
There he is.

00:47.505 --> 00:50.717
The man of the hour
has officially arrived.

00:50.717 --> 00:52.135
Let me just say how good it is

00:52.135 --> 00:53.887
to finally meet ya, Sam.

00:55.263 --> 00:57.849
(gentle music)

01:12.197 --> 01:16.658
♪ Said the thief to the moon ♪

01:16.658 --> 01:21.664
♪ I'll extinguish your light soon ♪

01:21.914 --> 01:26.920
♪ I'll put an end to all
the light that you shed ♪

01:27.420 --> 01:32.425
♪ On this world in its darkened state ♪

01:34.761 --> 01:39.515
♪ Said the moon to the thief ♪

01:39.515 --> 01:44.354
♪ You know not of what you seek ♪

01:44.354 --> 01:49.359
♪ You'll doom the world
to wander the night ♪

01:49.609 --> 01:54.614
♪ With no light to guide
the paths that men seek ♪

01:56.074 --> 02:01.079
♪ Oh but all the wealth in
the world will be mine ♪

02:05.917 --> 02:07.919
- [Sam] You swing like a girl.

02:11.297 --> 02:14.592
Jesus Christ, you look like shit.

02:22.642 --> 02:26.312
- [Jimmy] Yeah well you're
still fucking short.

02:26.312 --> 02:28.064
Even with those lifts in your boots.

02:31.151 --> 02:33.820
(both laughing)

02:35.655 --> 02:36.614
- [Sam] Look at you.

02:36.614 --> 02:39.200
God damn, you look like my sister.

02:39.200 --> 02:40.785
- [Jimmy] I know, tell me about it.

02:40.785 --> 02:41.619
Why, is she hot?

02:42.495 --> 02:43.621
- [Sam] Eh, she's better looking than you.

02:43.621 --> 02:45.123
- [Jimmy] It's nice you came to visit.

02:47.542 --> 02:49.002
You can leave that open.

02:49.002 --> 02:51.421
- [Sam] Yeah, you should
probably let this place air out.

02:53.381 --> 02:54.465
- [Jimmy] Want a beer?

02:55.925 --> 02:59.053
- [Sam] Ah shit man, is
there a fucking choice?

02:59.053 --> 03:00.513
- [Jimmy] Not really.

03:03.766 --> 03:06.019
- Welcome to paradise.

03:07.187 --> 03:09.063
- [Sam] Paradise, is that
what we're calling this place?

03:09.063 --> 03:09.898
Okay

03:10.982 --> 03:12.233
- [Jimmy] How've you been?

03:13.651 --> 03:15.361
How's the misses?

03:15.361 --> 03:16.196
How's your mom?

03:19.949 --> 03:20.783
Sorry buddy.

03:20.783 --> 03:21.868
- [Sam] Don't be sorry, man.

03:21.868 --> 03:23.161
It's all right.

03:23.161 --> 03:24.495
Cancer's a bitch, brother.

03:26.956 --> 03:29.292
- [Jimmy] Yeah, too bad some
things that could really help

03:29.292 --> 03:30.126
are illegal.

03:32.295 --> 03:34.964
- [Sam] That's actually what
I wanted to talk to you about.

03:37.716 --> 03:39.802
What are you doing for
money nowadays, Jimmy?

03:39.802 --> 03:42.055
- [Jimmy] Staying out of
trouble, that's what matters.

03:42.055 --> 03:44.682
- [Sam] Well, you remember
that second tour in Kandahar?

03:46.434 --> 03:47.518
Remember the village,

03:49.437 --> 03:50.897
the one with the marijuana fields?

03:51.814 --> 03:53.983
- [Jimmy] You trying to get
me to grow pot with you, Sam?

03:57.487 --> 04:00.240
- [Sam] Look, we learned
something major over there, man.

04:00.240 --> 04:02.492
You gonna tell me that putting that to use

04:02.492 --> 04:04.327
and making some money out of it,

04:06.704 --> 04:08.248
that's something you never thought of?

04:08.248 --> 04:09.249
- [Jimmy] I'm not your guy.

04:10.208 --> 04:11.042
- [Sam] No?

04:12.335 --> 04:15.838
No, you're right, I must be
mistaking you for the other guy

04:15.838 --> 04:17.839
with the foreclosure notice on his door.

04:19.676 --> 04:21.094
- [Jimmy] Thanks for the visit, Sam.

04:23.805 --> 04:25.932
- [Sam] Look, Jimmy, what
are you gonna do, huh?

04:25.932 --> 04:27.934
At some point, someone is
gonna come and kick you out

04:27.934 --> 04:30.103
of your paradise here.

04:31.145 --> 04:33.231
And then you're either
gonna end up back over there

04:33.231 --> 04:34.983
or somewhere worse.

04:34.983 --> 04:36.359
No hey, listen to me, look,

04:36.359 --> 04:37.902
I watched my mother wither away

04:37.902 --> 04:39.988
when I knew I could have
done something about it.

04:41.239 --> 04:42.490
I'm not talking about fucking
selling weed here, Jimmy,

04:42.490 --> 04:45.284
I'm talking about doing
something real. Okay?

04:45.284 --> 04:48.454
Cancer? It's curable.

04:48.454 --> 04:51.457
It's more of a business
than it is a disease.

04:51.457 --> 04:54.127
(ominous music)

04:55.753 --> 04:56.713
- [Jimmy] You know those
weren't all marijuana fields

04:56.713 --> 04:57.797
out there in Kandahar.

04:59.173 --> 05:03.261
Half that was poppy. Opium fields.

05:05.054 --> 05:05.888
- [Sam] Exactly.

05:07.974 --> 05:10.977
(adventurous music)

05:37.211 --> 05:40.465
(classical rock music)

06:23.007 --> 06:25.051
- [Tim] Marijuana's only been
only illegal all these years

06:25.051 --> 06:27.804
because of the big fat douche bags

06:27.804 --> 06:29.097
running corporate America.

06:30.431 --> 06:35.395
(ominous music)
(breathing deeply)

06:43.861 --> 06:46.781
First, it was William Randolph Hearst

06:46.781 --> 06:47.865
looking to line of pockets

06:47.865 --> 06:49.951
of his newspaper empire with gold.

06:50.827 --> 06:52.703
Then in the '80s,

06:52.703 --> 06:54.831
pharmaceutical companies.

06:54.831 --> 06:55.915
They kept this shit,

06:58.876 --> 07:00.670
a schedule one narcotic,

07:00.670 --> 07:03.631
because it helps fight diseases
that they don't want cured.

07:04.715 --> 07:06.759
Because if they help heal everyone,

07:08.553 --> 07:11.931
who are they gonna get to buy the drugs?

07:15.017 --> 07:17.687
(ominous music)

07:20.189 --> 07:21.357
- [Sam] Look, what do you
think is gonna happen?

07:21.357 --> 07:22.191
What, they're gonna buy my research

07:22.191 --> 07:24.068
and start clinical trials?

07:24.068 --> 07:25.570
- [Amanda] You sound like
some tree hugging hippie.

07:25.570 --> 07:28.114
You do not know what's gonna happen.

07:28.114 --> 07:29.699
- [Sam] Oh I don't, huh?

07:30.616 --> 07:32.534
- [Amanda] No, you don't, Sam.

07:32.534 --> 07:33.369
Do you ever think

07:33.369 --> 07:35.413
you just don't want to see
your work come to an end?

07:35.413 --> 07:37.290
I love your passion, but
what's the point of all this

07:37.290 --> 07:39.459
if you're just gonna
hold your work hostage?

07:43.087 --> 07:45.339
- [Sam] Let's not forget here, Amanda,

07:45.339 --> 07:46.757
I grow marijuana, all right?

07:48.092 --> 07:50.052
- [Amanda] Excuse me, I
do not give my husband up

07:50.052 --> 07:51.220
four nights a week

07:51.220 --> 07:52.847
for marijuana.

07:54.765 --> 07:55.808
You know Mrs. Singer?

07:56.933 --> 07:58.186
- [Sam] Yeah, yeah, she's the one

07:58.186 --> 08:00.646
that calls me Kevin Bacon, right?

08:00.646 --> 08:02.315
Wait, she didn't?

08:02.315 --> 08:04.108
- [Amanda] She went into
remission this week.

08:05.109 --> 08:07.820
- [Sam] She's stage four
pancreatic, that's impossible.

08:07.820 --> 08:08.905
- [Amanda] They're calling it a miracle.

08:08.905 --> 08:11.073
All the doctors are taking credit for it.

08:11.073 --> 08:13.284
In reality, I've been
giving her your CBD extract

08:13.284 --> 08:14.619
for the past three months.

08:15.828 --> 08:16.662
- [Sam] Amanda, you've been administering

08:16.662 --> 08:17.497
my formula to patients?

08:19.165 --> 08:20.917
- [Amanda] Look, I know we
said we weren't going to,

08:20.917 --> 08:22.668
but babe, it works.

08:22.668 --> 08:23.503
- [Sam] No, no, no, look, that is

08:23.503 --> 08:24.587
it's far from FDA approved.

08:24.587 --> 08:27.632
You can get in a lot of
trouble if you get caught.

08:27.632 --> 08:29.258
- [Amanda] Well maybe it'd be legal

08:29.258 --> 08:32.303
if you started playing ball
with the rest of the world.

08:32.303 --> 08:34.972
(ominous music)

08:36.849 --> 08:40.061
Look, I know you have your reasons.

08:40.061 --> 08:42.104
- [Sam] No, we're not talking about that.

08:44.482 --> 08:47.026
- [Nurse] Hey Amanda, Barry
wants to see you in his office.

08:48.319 --> 08:49.153
- [Amanda] I got to go.

08:49.153 --> 08:50.530
I'll call you back later, bye.

08:51.906 --> 08:54.283
- [Sam] Yeah? Love you too.

08:55.660 --> 08:58.496
(ominous music)

08:58.496 --> 09:02.291
- [Ace] You lose 50K at
one of Mr. Black's tables.

09:02.291 --> 09:04.418
Now that's just fine, hell that's dandy.

09:04.418 --> 09:06.379
We see that kind of thing all the time.

09:06.379 --> 09:09.257
We extend you a line of credit
to make your money back.

09:09.257 --> 09:12.009
We don't need to do that, but we did.

09:12.009 --> 09:13.636
You make your money back.

09:13.636 --> 09:15.346
You make our money back.

09:15.346 --> 09:17.056
Time to settle up and walk away.

09:17.056 --> 09:19.225
But you didn't settle up now did you boy?

09:19.225 --> 09:21.018
You did not walk away.

09:22.812 --> 09:25.189
- [Parker] It's gambling,
that's how it works sometimes.

09:25.189 --> 09:27.733
(laughing)

09:27.733 --> 09:28.568
- [Ace] You hear that?

09:28.568 --> 09:30.653
He's trying to tell me how gambling works.

09:30.653 --> 09:32.321
- [Parker] Ah, God damn it.

09:34.699 --> 09:37.827
- [Ace] Oh. Evening boss.

09:37.827 --> 09:42.832
- [Mr. Black] Well, well, Mr.
Renfro. How are we tonight?

09:43.332 --> 09:44.165
- [Parker] Please, I was telling your man,

09:44.165 --> 09:45.001
I can get you your money.

09:47.169 --> 09:48.588
- [Mr. Black] These things
really start to blur together

09:48.588 --> 09:49.422
after a while, don't they?

09:49.422 --> 09:52.383
- [Ace] That they do, boss. That they do.

09:52.383 --> 09:53.217
- [Mr. Black] Unfortunately,
you know how many guys

09:53.217 --> 09:54.051
sat in that chair

09:56.095 --> 09:58.097
and told me the same load of horse crap?

09:58.097 --> 10:01.183
- [Parker] I know. I understand
that, but I can deliver,

10:01.183 --> 10:03.102
you just got to give me a couple days.

10:04.729 --> 10:05.563
- [Mr. Black] What's he owe?

10:05.563 --> 10:06.897
- [Ace] About $100,000.

10:08.190 --> 10:11.110
- [Mr. Black] Whoa,
rich blood, Mr. Renfro.

10:12.862 --> 10:15.197
How do you plan on paying
me back in a couple of days?

10:16.157 --> 10:17.241
Mommy and daddy

10:18.951 --> 10:20.286
or back to the fucking tables?

10:22.747 --> 10:24.165
That's what I thought, Ace.

10:24.165 --> 10:24.999
- [Ace] Yes, sir.

10:26.208 --> 10:29.045
- [Parker] Marijuana, marijuana, hey.

10:29.045 --> 10:29.879
- [Mr. Black] You want
to pay me back 100 grand

10:29.879 --> 10:30.713
in marijuana?

10:31.922 --> 10:33.507
- [Parker] More, double,
triple, just make him stop.

10:33.507 --> 10:34.967
- [Mr. Black] Hold up, Ace.

10:34.967 --> 10:36.469
- [Parker] Fuck, thank God.

10:36.469 --> 10:38.804
- [Ace] I would not thank God just yet.

10:38.804 --> 10:39.972
- [Mr. Black] He's right.

10:39.972 --> 10:41.557
My curiosity doesn't last that long.

10:41.557 --> 10:42.391
- [Ace] No.

10:44.143 --> 10:45.895
- [Parker] Okay so my grandma
has this ranch, all right?

10:45.895 --> 10:48.522
And a few years ago she
took on this new tenant,

10:48.522 --> 10:50.733
this medical marijuana collective.

10:50.733 --> 10:51.817
- [Mr. Black] Are you trying to tell us

10:51.817 --> 10:53.736
that your granny owns a pot farm?

10:55.071 --> 10:57.782
- Oh, kid, I may be a lot of things,

10:57.782 --> 11:00.368
but a pot dealer ain't
on the fucking list.

11:00.368 --> 11:01.827
- [Parker] You don't understand.

11:01.827 --> 11:03.621
This guy, Sam Paxton,

11:03.621 --> 11:05.414
he's an ex military guy.

11:05.414 --> 11:06.874
He must've picked up some tricks from Iraq

11:06.874 --> 11:09.794
'cause he's got this formula.

11:09.794 --> 11:11.587
I don't know what he's splicing it with,

11:11.587 --> 11:14.006
but apparently, this shit,

11:14.006 --> 11:15.925
it fights cancer like a mother fucker.

11:17.009 --> 11:18.886
- [Ace] What's he using, Miracle Grow?

11:20.262 --> 11:22.640
- [Mr. Black] What do you
mean it fights cancer?

11:22.640 --> 11:24.684
- [Parker] Apparently the
entire medical industry

11:24.684 --> 11:25.935
is trying to cut a deal with him,

11:25.935 --> 11:28.938
but he won't do it 'cause of
some hippy-dippy bullshit.

11:28.938 --> 11:30.731
- [Mr. Black] How do I
know this ain't bullshit?

11:32.608 --> 11:33.567
- [Parker] That guy,

11:33.567 --> 11:36.070
the black guy, who always sits
at your high stakes table.

11:36.070 --> 11:38.489
His face is in all those magazines.

11:38.489 --> 11:40.324
Ask Ace. Ace, you know
who I'm talking about.

11:40.324 --> 11:41.534
- [Ace] I think he's talking
about Carter Winslow, boss.

11:41.534 --> 11:43.703
- [Mr. Black] I know who he's
talking about, thank you.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.454
- [Parker] Ask him if it's legit.

11:45.454 --> 11:47.081
I bet he tried to cut a deal himself.

11:51.085 --> 11:52.086
- [Mr. Black] Don't go anywhere.

11:56.757 --> 11:59.427
(phone ringing)

12:03.013 --> 12:05.891
Mr. Winslow, how are you, my friend?

12:05.891 --> 12:06.892
- [Carter] Caesar?

12:06.892 --> 12:08.936
- Heard you took me for a
ride on the tables tonight.

12:08.936 --> 12:09.895
(Carter laughing)

12:09.895 --> 12:11.147
That's okay.

12:11.147 --> 12:13.983
Usually finds its way
back one play or another.

12:13.983 --> 12:14.817
- [Carter] Yeah.

12:14.817 --> 12:15.651
- Listen my friend,

12:15.651 --> 12:16.485
I have a question for you.

12:16.485 --> 12:17.319
- [Carter] What's that?

12:17.319 --> 12:18.362
- Call it a hypothetical.

12:18.362 --> 12:20.781
(sexy music)

12:26.203 --> 12:27.997
- [Carter] You're talking
about the Paxton research,

12:27.997 --> 12:29.039
I know it.

12:30.291 --> 12:31.876
It might as well be a myth.

12:31.876 --> 12:35.713
Problem is the tribe wants
to sell. The chief doesn't.

12:36.797 --> 12:39.383
Seems like he's a man without a price.

12:41.719 --> 12:44.388
(ominous music)

12:50.186 --> 12:51.979
Attend me closely, Caesar.

12:53.105 --> 12:55.024
The one who gets me that formula,

12:56.108 --> 13:01.113
be it the chief, one of the
little Indians or somebody else,

13:01.781 --> 13:06.786
that person will be very,
very well compensated.

13:08.078 --> 13:10.664
- [Mr. Black] All right, we'll talk soon.

13:15.169 --> 13:18.380
All right kid, what am I gonna
find on granny's pot farm?

13:18.380 --> 13:19.256
What kind of security we talking about?

13:19.256 --> 13:20.633
- [Parker] Chain link fence.

13:20.633 --> 13:22.176
- [Mr. Black] Local PD?

13:22.176 --> 13:23.969
- [Parker] 30 miles away at best.

13:26.347 --> 13:27.473
- [Mr. Black] All right, Mr. Renfro,

13:27.473 --> 13:29.892
you got 48 hours to get
granny off that farm.

13:29.892 --> 13:31.685
Can you do that for me?

13:31.685 --> 13:33.979
- [Parker] Well, what
happens after 48 hours?

13:33.979 --> 13:35.439
- [Mr. Black] Cut him loose.

13:35.439 --> 13:37.399
- [Parker] What happens after 48 hours?

13:37.399 --> 13:38.359
(grunting)

13:40.444 --> 13:43.614
- [Tim] All right, I'm gonna
hit the john real quick.

13:43.614 --> 13:44.448
- [Jesse] Sure you are.

13:46.575 --> 13:47.409
- [Ernie] His formula?

13:49.745 --> 13:51.789
We've been working on
this for three years,

13:51.789 --> 13:54.875
we. Me, him, you...

13:54.875 --> 13:56.627
- [Red] You know what I mean.

13:56.627 --> 13:57.753
- [Ernie] Well it's too late anyway,

13:57.753 --> 13:58.838
the ball's already rolling.

13:58.838 --> 14:00.714
- [Red] We haven't
handed anything over yet.

14:02.383 --> 14:05.427
- [Jane] Ladies, what are we doing here?

14:05.427 --> 14:07.346
- [Dr. Altman] Now I know
that this is gonna sound

14:07.346 --> 14:08.556
just shy of deplorable,

14:08.556 --> 14:09.807
but you know it and I know it,

14:09.807 --> 14:11.934
that lovely, lovely woman back there

14:11.934 --> 14:13.936
should have been in the dirt months ago.

14:15.312 --> 14:17.314
Now before I go in there
and ask Mrs. Seeger

14:17.314 --> 14:20.359
why her hail Mary's are
different than the rest,

14:20.359 --> 14:23.195
maybe you can shed a little
light on what I saw earlier.

14:24.780 --> 14:28.617
- [Amanda] We're taking
miracle completely out of it?

14:28.617 --> 14:29.994
- [Dr. Altman] Not if by miracle

14:29.994 --> 14:32.454
you mean your husband's
marijuana research, no.

14:34.915 --> 14:36.792
Look Amanda, I know you mean to help

14:38.168 --> 14:40.337
and although I don't doubt
you're onto something here,

14:40.337 --> 14:42.339
you cannot give my patients weed.

14:43.299 --> 14:46.135
- [Amanda] It was a
concentrated CBD extract.

14:46.135 --> 14:47.887
- [Dr. Altman] It's not what I prescribed.

14:47.887 --> 14:49.847
- [Amanda] Then why
don't you prescribe it?

14:49.847 --> 14:52.016
Oh that's right because it's
not made by one of them.

14:53.225 --> 14:54.602
- [Dr. Altman] Excuse me?

14:54.602 --> 14:55.811
- [Amanda] I'm sorry,
that was out of line.

14:55.811 --> 14:57.354
- [Dr. Altman] No, you listen to me.

14:58.522 --> 15:00.900
There was a time that I
was young and naive too,

15:00.900 --> 15:02.067
and I had what I thought

15:02.067 --> 15:04.278
were good ideas and great intentions.

15:05.362 --> 15:07.323
But out here in the real world,

15:07.323 --> 15:10.075
we professional people have
to play along with these rules

15:10.075 --> 15:12.494
that were put in place
long before we were here.

15:13.579 --> 15:16.498
And until your CBD extract

15:16.498 --> 15:19.084
is packaged and labeled as a medicine,

15:20.044 --> 15:21.879
it's still weed, my dear.

15:24.965 --> 15:27.426
Now why don't you take
the rest of the afternoon

15:27.426 --> 15:29.470
and go and review your job requirements?

15:30.638 --> 15:32.348
- [Amanda] I don't think
that that'll be necessary.

15:32.348 --> 15:35.225
- [Dr. Altman] That is
not a suggestion, Amanda.

15:36.518 --> 15:38.479
(ominous music)

15:38.479 --> 15:40.064
- [Ernie] We weren't here yesterday.

15:40.064 --> 15:42.858
Jane's been the one drowning the plants.

15:42.858 --> 15:43.692
- [Jane] Yeah?

15:43.692 --> 15:45.194
How about you come water these plants

15:45.194 --> 15:47.780
and I'll make doodles on the clipboard?

15:47.780 --> 15:50.449
(ominous music)

15:57.456 --> 16:01.543
- [Sam] Hey. Any of you guys
seen the old lady at all today?

16:01.543 --> 16:02.711
Has she been floating around?

16:02.711 --> 16:04.213
- [Red] Are we supposed to?

16:04.213 --> 16:06.674
She always just stays in her room anyway.

16:06.674 --> 16:08.092
- [Ernie] That worthless grandson of her's

16:08.092 --> 16:09.677
ever stop by this week?

16:11.261 --> 16:13.180
- Yeah, yeah, he was here.

16:13.180 --> 16:15.224
His face was all bruised up actually.

16:17.685 --> 16:18.978
- [Ernie] You tell him to fuck off?

16:20.688 --> 16:23.357
(ominous music)

16:29.530 --> 16:32.783
- [Sam] Yeah, yeah, of course.

16:32.783 --> 16:35.452
(ominous music)

16:44.962 --> 16:47.881
