1:03:11.621 --> 1:03:13.748
- [Parker] Well, what
happens after 48 hours?

1:03:13.748 --> 1:03:15.374
- [Mr. Black] Cut him loose.

1:03:15.374 --> 1:03:17.293
- [Parker] What happens after 48 hours?

1:03:17.293 --> 1:03:19.754
(Parker grunting)

1:03:19.754 --> 1:03:22.465
- [Jimmy] So let me get this straight,

1:03:22.465 --> 1:03:25.843
you're asking me to take out
seven men inside of a minute?

1:03:25.843 --> 1:03:27.428
- [Ace] Asking?

1:03:27.428 --> 1:03:28.763
Hell, we're telling.

1:03:29.931 --> 1:03:32.517
I thought you had some laundry
list of confirmed kills.

1:03:32.517 --> 1:03:36.145
Isn't this sort of thing supposed
to be in your wheelhouse?

1:03:36.145 --> 1:03:38.940
Now we were gonna give you
70 large for doing this,

1:03:38.940 --> 1:03:41.067
but now, you see,

1:03:41.067 --> 1:03:42.193
now I'm getting a sudden urge

1:03:42.193 --> 1:03:45.780
to make our little arrangement
here performance based.

1:03:45.780 --> 1:03:46.614
I'mma tell you what,

1:03:46.614 --> 1:03:48.908
we're gonna give you 10 grand
for every head you splatter

1:03:48.908 --> 1:03:51.202
before we roll in with the cleanup crew.

1:03:51.202 --> 1:03:53.538
You go seven for seven now,

1:03:53.538 --> 1:03:55.206
I'll personally guarantee you 80.

1:03:56.207 --> 1:03:57.708
- [Jimmy] Sounds good.

1:03:57.708 --> 1:03:58.668
Anything else?

1:03:59.627 --> 1:04:00.962
- [Ace] We good here, boss?

1:04:03.631 --> 1:04:08.010
- [Mr. Black] The leader. This Sam Paxton.

1:04:10.137 --> 1:04:11.806
I want him alive.

1:04:11.806 --> 1:04:15.685
You wound him, but he's
alive when we get there.

1:04:16.561 --> 1:04:17.395
You got that?

1:04:19.063 --> 1:04:21.315
- [Jimmy] And how am I supposed
to know which one he is?

1:04:22.567 --> 1:04:23.568
- [Mr. Black] I'm sure
you've found yourself

1:04:23.568 --> 1:04:25.570
in a police lineup or two.

1:04:25.570 --> 1:04:28.364
Figure it out, okay slick?

1:04:28.364 --> 1:04:30.032
- [Ace] You can go now.

1:04:30.032 --> 1:04:32.785
(ominous music)

1:04:34.120 --> 1:04:37.456
- [Mr. Black] Oh and Ace,
let's find out if our guy's a

1:04:37.456 --> 1:04:40.293
family man. We're gonna
need some insurance.

1:04:40.293 --> 1:04:44.380
- [Ace] You know boss,
I'll notify Carl and Willy

1:04:44.380 --> 1:04:45.756
to pick up the next of kin,

1:04:45.756 --> 1:04:48.050
but may I ask our of pure curiosity,

1:04:48.050 --> 1:04:49.719
why are we leaving this man alive?

1:04:51.470 --> 1:04:53.973
- [Mr. Black] If you knew the
six winning jackpot numbers,

1:04:55.391 --> 1:04:59.312
but for some reason you're not cashing in,

1:04:59.312 --> 1:05:01.731
would you write down all six,

1:05:01.731 --> 1:05:04.150
leave 'em around for two
crooks like us to steal

1:05:06.152 --> 1:05:08.279
or would you put down five

1:05:08.279 --> 1:05:10.072
and leave one in the safe up here?

1:05:11.073 --> 1:05:13.951
That, plus I'd just
like to know the reason.

1:05:15.036 --> 1:05:16.120
- [Ace] The reason boss?

1:05:17.663 --> 1:05:19.624
- [Mr. Black] Why is
this man not cashing in?

1:05:23.210 --> 1:05:25.880
(phone ringing)

1:05:32.678 --> 1:05:33.638
- [Jimmy] Sam, pick up.

1:05:39.727 --> 1:05:41.020
- [Amanda] Yeah, hello?

1:05:42.438 --> 1:05:45.107
(ominous music)

1:05:50.696 --> 1:05:53.324
- [Jimmy] Hey Sam, been a bit, bro.

1:05:56.118 --> 1:06:00.247
Oh by the way, been a gun
for hire the last three years

1:06:04.085 --> 1:06:04.961
and my latest job

1:06:06.587 --> 1:06:08.214
is to kill you and all your men.

1:06:11.884 --> 1:06:13.094
But how you been?

1:06:17.932 --> 1:06:18.766
You know brother,

1:06:20.476 --> 1:06:21.310
I bet neither of us

1:06:21.310 --> 1:06:23.604
figured the paths of our
bad choices would cross.

1:06:29.819 --> 1:06:31.821
- [Tim] And then he said,
Charlie M or something,

1:06:31.821 --> 1:06:33.489
I don't know.

1:06:33.489 --> 1:06:34.740
It was weird.

1:06:34.740 --> 1:06:37.326
- [Amanda] Charlie M, what is that?

1:06:37.326 --> 1:06:39.161
- [Tim] It's from the movie "Casino".

1:06:39.161 --> 1:06:39.996
You ever seen "Casino"?

1:06:39.996 --> 1:06:41.247
- [Amanda] No.

1:06:41.247 --> 1:06:44.542
- [Tim] Yeah it's weird, I don't know.

1:06:44.542 --> 1:06:46.252
- [Amanda] Is this over now?

1:06:46.252 --> 1:06:48.004
- [Sam] I got to get you somewhere safe.

1:06:48.004 --> 1:06:50.006
- [Amanda] Are you gonna
tell me what's going on?

1:06:51.924 --> 1:06:55.136
(ominous music)

1:06:55.136 --> 1:06:56.637
- [Sam] It was Jimmy.

1:06:56.637 --> 1:06:58.973
- [Amanda] Jimmy, your
old war buddy, Jimmy?

1:07:00.933 --> 1:07:01.851
He did all this?

1:07:01.851 --> 1:07:06.022
- [Sam] Well yeah, he's also
the reason we're still alive.

1:07:06.022 --> 1:07:07.773
- [Amanda] Great, I'll be sure to send him

1:07:07.773 --> 1:07:08.983
a thank you letter.

1:07:10.401 --> 1:07:11.777
- [Sam] What about you Tim?

1:07:13.487 --> 1:07:14.697
- [Tim] All I know

1:07:14.697 --> 1:07:16.782
is I don't want to see that
fucking maniac ever again.

1:07:19.410 --> 1:07:23.456
But besides, someone's got to stick around

1:07:23.456 --> 1:07:24.540
and water the plants.

1:07:27.043 --> 1:07:27.877
- [Sam] Hey, I'm sorry.

1:07:30.087 --> 1:07:32.006
I'm sorry I couldn't get to before um,

1:07:34.341 --> 1:07:35.760
before all this.

1:07:38.804 --> 1:07:40.681
- [Tim] I'm still breathing, right?

1:07:40.681 --> 1:07:43.350
(ominous music)

1:07:58.240 --> 1:07:59.075
- [Sam] Are you okay?

1:08:00.701 --> 1:08:02.745
You haven't said anything the whole ride.

1:08:04.747 --> 1:08:08.501
- [Amanda] I have a lot
of unanswered questions.

1:08:10.836 --> 1:08:12.880
I know you're the victim,

1:08:14.215 --> 1:08:17.384
but that monster

1:08:17.384 --> 1:08:22.389
seemed like he was going
to expose you, Sam,

1:08:22.389 --> 1:08:24.850
as if he knew some sort of secret.

1:08:24.850 --> 1:08:26.519
- [Sam] What secret?

1:08:26.519 --> 1:08:27.560
- [Amanda] I don't know,

1:08:27.560 --> 1:08:29.772
but when he held a fucking gun to my head

1:08:29.772 --> 1:08:32.023
it seemed as if you were
about to blurt it out.

1:08:33.651 --> 1:08:34.485
- [Sam] We're there.

1:08:35.944 --> 1:08:36.862
- [Amanda] Of course we are.

1:08:41.617 --> 1:08:42.576
So what's the plan?

1:08:48.332 --> 1:08:49.166
- [Sam] Hey.

1:08:50.501 --> 1:08:52.128
- [Amanda] That's your plan?

1:08:52.128 --> 1:08:53.379
That's the plan?

1:08:53.379 --> 1:08:55.714
- [Sam] You're not gonna have to use it.

1:08:55.714 --> 1:08:59.050
But if you do, it's just like the range.

1:09:01.679 --> 1:09:04.014
(cocks gun)

1:09:08.144 --> 1:09:12.857
Hey, unless you hear
anything, stay here. Okay?

1:09:16.193 --> 1:09:17.903
- [Amanda] I guess
we'll finish this later.

1:09:22.825 --> 1:09:23.658
- [Sam] Noscapine.

1:09:25.244 --> 1:09:26.370
- [Amanda] Nosca, what?

1:09:26.370 --> 1:09:28.121
- [Sam] If you reverse engineer opium,

1:09:28.121 --> 1:09:29.832
you can isolate a compound called

1:09:29.832 --> 1:09:30.666
noscapine.

1:09:31.666 --> 1:09:32.626
It's not an addictive pain killer,

1:09:32.626 --> 1:09:34.420
so big pharma's got no use for it,

1:09:35.504 --> 1:09:37.505
but it inhibits cancer cells.

1:09:37.505 --> 1:09:40.259
(ominous music)

1:09:45.431 --> 1:09:46.264
- [Amanda] What?

1:09:49.768 --> 1:09:50.935
(Amanda sighs)

1:09:50.935 --> 1:09:54.023
(ominous music)

1:10:21.133 --> 1:10:23.469
(pulls gun)

1:10:35.856 --> 1:10:38.692
(dramatic music)

1:10:46.075 --> 1:10:47.493
- [Sam] Oh Jesus, fuck.

1:10:47.493 --> 1:10:49.245
(gunfire blasting)

1:10:49.245 --> 1:10:51.080
- [Amanda] Fuck, what the fuck?

1:10:52.748 --> 1:10:53.582
- [Jimmy] Sam?

1:10:53.582 --> 1:10:55.541
- [Sam] Put the fucking gun down, man.

1:10:55.541 --> 1:10:56.377
What the fuck?

1:10:56.377 --> 1:10:57.460
Hey Jimmy-

1:10:57.460 --> 1:10:58.295
- [Jimmy] What the fuck
are you doing here?

1:10:58.295 --> 1:11:00.505
- [Sam] Put the fucking gun down.

1:11:00.505 --> 1:11:02.591
Jesus Christ, hey look.

1:11:02.591 --> 1:11:03.675
Oh my. Fuck.

1:11:13.559 --> 1:11:15.312
Jesus fucking christ.

1:11:22.778 --> 1:11:25.739
Nah, come on man, this is bullshit.

1:11:27.157 --> 1:11:28.200
- [Jimmy] You find my letter?

1:11:30.035 --> 1:11:31.620
- [Sam] Yeah man, I found your letter.

1:11:34.832 --> 1:11:36.083
- [Jimmy] I'm sorry, I didn't know.

1:11:36.083 --> 1:11:37.251
- [Sam] Hey Jimmy look,

1:11:37.251 --> 1:11:38.585
I said I found the letter.

1:11:44.258 --> 1:11:45.300
- [Jimmy] Well if you're
not here to kill me,

1:11:45.300 --> 1:11:46.135
what do you want?

1:11:47.636 --> 1:11:49.972
- [Sam] I take it your
boss is still alive?

1:11:51.639 --> 1:11:52.558
- [Jimmy] You don't want to go there.

1:11:52.558 --> 1:11:57.563
- [Sam] I want my family safe. All right?

1:11:57.646 --> 1:11:59.481
The way I see it,

1:11:59.481 --> 1:12:02.651
you don't get to take your
life, until I take his.

1:12:04.528 --> 1:12:06.989
Now you gonna put that fucking gun down?

1:12:09.241 --> 1:12:11.910
(ominous music)

1:12:14.955 --> 1:12:18.834
- [Amanda] Stop pointing
that gun at my husband.

1:12:18.834 --> 1:12:20.002
- [Sam] It's not for me.

1:12:21.170 --> 1:12:23.839
(ominous music)

1:12:25.132 --> 1:12:27.175
- [Jimmy] Sorry about
this whole mess, darlin'.

1:12:30.219 --> 1:12:32.681
- [Amanda] Just put it down, Jimmy.

1:12:32.681 --> 1:12:35.351
(ominous music)

1:12:43.901 --> 1:12:45.903
- Wasted my last bullet on you anyways.

1:12:47.862 --> 1:12:52.576
- [Sam] So this Mr.
Black, how do we get him?

1:12:52.576 --> 1:12:55.412
(dramatic music)

1:13:03.629 --> 1:13:05.339
- [Jimmy] If you're guessing
Black was a fake name,

1:13:05.339 --> 1:13:06.882
you're right.

1:13:06.882 --> 1:13:08.425
His real name is Caesar Bonnano,

1:13:09.635 --> 1:13:11.594
bastard of the Bonnano crime family.

1:13:12.471 --> 1:13:13.680
His father was an Italian

1:13:13.680 --> 1:13:15.057
and his mother was a Jew,

1:13:15.057 --> 1:13:16.517
making him a half-breed,

1:13:17.893 --> 1:13:20.020
meaning he could only
rise so far in the mafia

1:13:20.020 --> 1:13:20.896
and he knew that.

1:13:21.939 --> 1:13:24.566
So, changed his name, moved out west.

1:13:25.984 --> 1:13:27.568
His mob ties have loosened over the years.

1:13:27.568 --> 1:13:29.571
So long as he kicks back
something every now and again,

1:13:29.571 --> 1:13:30.823
he's his own boss.

1:13:33.282 --> 1:13:37.246
- [Sam] Family? Wife? Kids?

1:13:37.246 --> 1:13:39.164
- [Jimmy] He's got a
daughter, pretty smart kid.

1:13:39.164 --> 1:13:41.125
She goes to Cal-Tech.

1:13:41.125 --> 1:13:43.669
Wife though, doesn't leave the house much.

1:13:43.669 --> 1:13:44.503
- [Sam] No?

1:13:45.379 --> 1:13:47.423
- [Jimmy] She's got stage three leukemia.

1:13:48.549 --> 1:13:50.759
By the looks of it,
she's losing the battle.

1:13:50.759 --> 1:13:53.262
- [Amanda] Explains why
he's so obsessed with you.

1:13:53.262 --> 1:13:54.096
- [Sam] Hmm.

1:13:55.180 --> 1:13:56.557
Where do we find him?

1:13:56.557 --> 1:13:58.434
- [Jimmy] He also runs an
underground gambling racket

1:13:58.434 --> 1:13:59.934
outside of Los Angeles.

1:14:01.186 --> 1:14:04.022
His high stakes tables bring
in some pretty high rollers.

1:14:05.065 --> 1:14:07.901
That's padded the man's ego quite a bit.

1:14:07.901 --> 1:14:09.820
Although they still think he's a crook.

1:14:11.487 --> 1:14:13.282
He doesn't like that either.

1:14:13.282 --> 1:14:15.868
(jazz music)

1:14:45.689 --> 1:14:47.483
- [Mr. Black] Carter, welcome.

1:14:50.527 --> 1:14:52.154
- [Carter] Nice to see you, Caesar.

1:14:53.947 --> 1:14:55.073
- [Mr. Black] Charlie,
